WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.800
Stop babysitting AI coding work.
AI coding does not lack models.
It lacks a command tower.

00:03.800 --> 00:07.800
See the live board before you trust the run.
One request becomes one visible workflow case
and one proof trail instead of disappearing
into scattered chats and shell logs.

00:07.800 --> 00:11.000
From PM request to proof trail.
Keep the handoff visible:
one task enters, one live board tracks the run,
and one proof lane stays ready for review or rerun.

00:11.000 --> 00:14.000
Use the same loop from the macOS desktop shell.
Keep the same board, proof surface,
and operator shortcuts aligned
when you want a native shell.

00:14.000 --> 00:18.000
Inspect before you trust.
Repo-backed today. Start with one proven workflow.
Inspect the live board first, then open
deeper docs only when the real job needs them.
